Next we move to the third part of the theorem concerning the relative entropy of entanglement. We ﬁrst prove two lemmas.

Lemma 3 Consider the class of superoperators
T (ρ) = aiUiρUi†,
i
where all Ui are unitary, and the ai form a distribution. Then, for any state ρ that is invariant under T , we have for the relative entropy:
S(ρ||σ) ≥ S(ρ||T †(σ)).

Proof. The proof of this lemma is heavily inspired by theorem 6 in Rains [11]. From S(ρ) = S(T (ρ)), we ﬁnd
S(ρ||σ) = Tr ρ log ρ − Tr ρ log σ = Tr ρ log ρ − Tr T (ρ) log σ = Tr ρ log ρ − ai Tr UiρUi† log σ
i
= Tr ρ log ρ − ai Tr ρ log(Ui†σU − i)
i
≥ Tr ρ log ρ − Tr ρ log( aiUi†σU − i)
i
= S(ρ||T †(σ)),

where in the penultimate line, we have used the subadditivity of the relative entropy w.r.t. its second argument.

Lemma 4 For ρ of the form ρ = U ΛU † with

 0√ 0 0√ 1 

U

=

  

